hip with Gambit, and Minerva goes to pure idea. X-Ceptional grabs Riches and explodes, killing them both.<ref>X-Men: Worst X-Man Ever #1\u20135</ref>\n\n=== Ultimate Marvel ===\nIn ''[[Ultimate X-Men]],'' the '''Academy of Tomorrow''' (previously called New Mutants) is founded by [[Emma Frost#Ultimate Marvel|Emma Frost]]. It is loosely linked to the X-Men via Emma Frost's professional relationship with her former lover and teacher [[Alternative versions of Professor X#Ultimate Charles Xavier|Charles Xavier]]. This Academy accepts any talented students, regardless of their genetic status. The team is headed by a non-telepathic and more pacifistic version of [[Emma Frost#Ultimate Marvel|Emma Frost]] and headed by field leader [[Havok (comics)#Ultimate Marvel|Havok]]. During ''[[Ultimatum (Ultimate Marvel)|Ultimatum]]'', the Academy of Tomorrow is destroyed in a terrorist attack by [[Jamie Madrox#Ultimate Marvel|Multiple Man]].<ref>''Ultimatum'' #3 (May 2009)</ref> Former members include [[Warren Worthington III#Ultimate Marvel|Angel]], Beast, [[Cannonball (comics)#Ultimate Marvel|Cannonball]], [[Cypher (comics)#Ultimate Marvel|Cypher]], [[Dazzler (Marvel Comics)#Ultimate Marvel|Dazzler]], [[Karma (comics)#Ultimate Marvel|Karma]], [[Northstar (Marvel Comics)|Northstar]], [[Polaris (Marvel Comics)#Ultimate Marvel|Polaris]], and [[Sunspot (comics)#Ultimate Marvel|Sunspot]].\n\n== In other media ==\n=== Television ===\n* The animated TV series ''[[X-Men: Evolution]]'' (2000\u20132003) featured a group called the New Mutants who, like their [[comic book]] counterparts, were a junior team living at the [[X-Mansion|Xavier Institute]] concurrently with the [[X-Men]]. The team featured [[Tabitha Smith#X-Men: Evolution|Boom-Boom]], [[Cannonball (comics)|Cannonball]], [[Magma (comics)|Magma]], [[Sunspot (comics)#Television|Sunspot]] and [[Wolfsbane (comics)|Wolfsbane]]. Other members, such as [[Berzerker (comics)|Berzerker]], [[Iceman (comics)|Iceman]], [[Jubilee (comics)|Jubilee]], and [[Jamie Madrox|Multiple Man]] were not New Mutants in the comic book series, but were featured in other X-Men comics. [[Danielle Moonstar|Mirage]] also appeared in the show's penultimate episode where she joined the team in a dream she projected into [[Shadowcat]]'s head.\n* ''New Mutants'' is the name given to the \"race\" of Mutants on the television show [[Mutant X (TV series)|Mutant X]].\n\n=== Film ===\n* The live-action film ''[[X-Men: Days of Future Past]]'' (2014) featured several of the New Mutants characters in supporting roles, namely [[Blink (comics)|Clarice Ferguson / Blink]], [[Warpath (comics)|James Proudstar / Warpath]], and [[Sunspot (comics)|Robert da Costa / Sunspot]] portrayed by [[Fan Bingbing]], [[Booboo Stewart]] and [[Adan Canto]], respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sKAP6Uv_pBU |title=X-Men: Days of Future Past Comic-Con 2013 \u2013 Full Panel|date=July 21, 2013|accessdate=September 1, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.empireonline.com/xmen/blink.asp |title=Empire X-Men: Days Of Future Past Exclusive \u2013 Blink Cover|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.empireonline.com/xmen/warpath.asp |title=Empire X-Men: Days Of Future Past Exclusive \u2013 Warpath Cover|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/adancanto/status/349260053230002177 |title=Twitter / adancanto: \"@ghosthunter: @X4X5Campaign I'm excited for @adancanto as Sunspot!!\" Thanks! Next summer.|author=Canto, Adan|date=June 24, 2013|accessdate=July 21, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.empireonline.com/xmen/sunspot.asp |title=Empire X-Men: Days Of Future Past Exclusive \u2013 Sunspot Cover|accessdate=January 30, 2014}}</ref>\n* {{main|The New Mutants (film)}} A [[The New Mutants (film)|film adaptation of the characters]] was released on August 28, 2020. The film was directed by [[Josh Boone (director)|Josh Boone]] with the script written by Boone and Knate Gwaltney and stars [[Maisie Williams]] as [[Wolfsbane (comics)|Wolfsbane]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BE9C09rk5O7/|title=Instagram photo by Josh Boone \u2022 May 3, 2016 at 5:40pm UTC|work=instagram.com}}</ref>, [[Anya Taylor-Joy]] as [[Magik (Illyana Rasputin)|Magik]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BE4k6tuk5KJ/|title=Instagram photo by Josh Boone \u2022 May 2, 2016 at 12:01am UTC|work=instagram.com}}</ref>, [[Charlie Heaton]] as [[Cannonball (comics)|Cannonball]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BE-BiDYE5I2/|title=Instagram photo by Josh Boone \u2022 May 4, 2016 at 2:48am UTC|work=instagram.com}}</ref> [[Henry Zaga]] as [[Sunspot (comics)|Sunspot]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BE-Bw7zk5JO/|title=Instagram photo by Josh Boone \u2022 May 4, 2016 at 2:50am UTC|work=instagram.com}}</ref> and [[Blu Hunt]] as [[Danielle Moonstar|Mirage]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BE9NvJnk5Ld/|title=Instagram photo by Josh Boone \u2022 May 3, 2016 at 7:15pm UTC|work=instagram.com}}</ref> as the members of the team.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hitfix.com/motion-captured/exclusive-are-these-josh-boones-first-three-new-mutants|title=EXCLUSIVE: Are These Josh Boone's First Three 'New Mutants'?|work=HitFix|last=McWeeny|first=Drew|date=March 31, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.superherohype.com/news/388435-new-mutants-movie-exclusive-anya-taylor-joy-says-james-mcavoy-will-star#/slide/1|title=New Mutants Movie Exclusive: Anya Taylor-Joy Says James McAvoy Will Star|publisher=Superhero Hype|last=Evry|first=Max|date=January 5, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | first=Adam | last=Chitwood | url=https://collider.com/new-mutants-movie-professor-x/ | title=\u2018New Mutants\u2019: Simon Kinberg Says Professor X Will Appear; Filming Could Begin Early 2017| website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] | date=May 10, 2016 | accessdate=10 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DRKEABr4DI8|ti